ertical-align:top; text-align:center;\"\n| style=\"width:400px;\" colspan=\"3\"| '''Set Details'''\n| style=\"width:400px; \" colspan=\"3\"| '''Special Features'''\n|- valign=\"top\"\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:left; width:400px;\"|\n* 15 Episodes\n* English, French and Spanish subtitles\n| colspan=\"3\" style=\"text-align:left; width:400px;\"|\n* Deleted Scenes - Unseen moments from Season 2\n* Bloopers\n|-\n| colspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''Release Dates'''\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[DVD region code#1|Region 1]]'''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[DVD region code#2|Region 2]]'''\n| colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''[[DVD region code#4|Region 4]]'''\n|- style=\"text-align:center;\"\n| colspan=\"2\"| June 21, 2016\n| colspan=\"2\"| November 14, 2016\n| colspan=\"2\"| {{TableTBA}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb title}}\n\n{{How to Get Away with Murder}}\n{{GLAAD Media Award for Outstanding Drama Series}}\n{{ABCNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n\n[[Category:2010s American LGBT-related drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American college television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American drama television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American legal television series]]\n[[Category:2010s American mystery television series]]\n[[Category:2014 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American Broadcasting Company original programming]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:GLAAD Media Award-winning programs]]\n[[Category:How to Get Away with Murder| ]]\n[[Category:Nonlinear narrative television series]]\n[[Category:Primetime Emmy Award-winning television series]]\n[[Category:Serial drama television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by ABC Studios]]\n[[Category:Television series by Shondaland]]\n[[Category:Television shows filmed in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Television shows set in Philadelphia]]\n[[Category:Transgender-related television programs]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Use American English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = How to Get Away with Murder\n| image                    = How To Get Away With Murder.svg\n| caption                  = \n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Legal drama]]\n* [[Mystery fiction|Mystery]]\n* [[Thriller (genre)|Thriller]]\n}}\n| creator                  = [[Peter Nowalk]]\n| starring                 = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Viola Davis]]\n* [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]]\n* [[Alfred Enoch]]\n* [[Jack Falahee]]\n* [[Katie Findlay]]\n* [[Aja Naomi King]]\n* [[Matt McGorry]]\n* [[Karla Souza]]\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]]\n* [[Liza Weil]]\n* [[Conrad Ricamora]]\n* [[Rome Flynn]]\n* [[Amirah Vann]]\n* [[Timothy Hutton]]\n}}\n| theme_music_composer     = [[Photek]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 6<!-- Number of seasons aired. Only update after a new season has been started. -->\n| num_episodes             = 86<!-- Number of episodes aired. Only update after a new episode has been broadcast. -->\n| list_episodes            = List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Shonda Rhimes]]\n* [[Betsy Beers]]\n* [[Bill D'Elia]]\n* Peter Nowalk\n}}\n| producer                 = {{Plainlist|\n* Scott Collins\n* Tracy Bellomo\n* Viola Davis\n}}\n| cinematography           = {{Plainlist|\n* Michael Price\n* Jeff Jur \n}}\n| editor                   = {{Plainlist|\n* David Greenspan\n* Philip Carr Neel\n* Julia Grove\n* Matthew Ramsey \n}}\n| camera                   = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 43 minutes\n| company                  = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Shondaland]]\n* NoWalk Entertainment\n* [[ABC Studios]]\n}}\n| distributor              = [[Disney\u2013ABC Domestic Television]]\n| channel                  = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| picture_format           = [[720p]] ([[High-definition television|HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = [[5.1 surround sound]]\n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2014|9|25}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n| related                  = \n| website                  = http://abc.go.com/shows/how-to-get-away-with-murder\n| website_title            = Official website\n| production_website       = \n}}\n\n'''''How to Get Away with Murder''''' is an American [[legal thriller]] television series that premiered on [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] on September 25, 2014.<ref name=\"Premiere\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-sets-fall-premiere-dates-718576 |title=ABC Sets Fall Premiere Dates |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=July 15, 2014 |accessdate=July 16, 2014 |first=Philiana |last=Ng |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140718032950/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-sets-fall-premiere-dates-718576 |archive-date=July 18, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><!-- defined by transclusion from List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes --> The series was created by [[Peter Nowalk]], and produced by [[Shonda Rhimes]] and [[ABC Studios]]. The series airs on ABC as part of a night of programming, all under Rhimes's [[Shondaland]] [[production company]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Adalian |first=Josef |url=https://www.vulture.com/2014/05/abc-is-creating-an-all-shonda-rhimes-thursday.html |title=ABC Is Creating an All\u2013Shonda Rhimes Thursday |work=Vulture |date=May 15, 2014 |accessdate=May 20, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514055621/https://www.vulture.com/2014/05/abc-is-creating-an-all-shonda-rhimes-thursday.html |archive-date=May 14, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Viola Davis]] stars as [[Annalise Keating]], a law professor at a prestigious [[Philadelphia]] university who, with five of her students, becomes entwined in a murder plot.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-orders-how-get-away-702523 |title=ABC Orders 'How to Get Away With Murder,' 'Black-ish,' 'American Crime,' 'Selfie,' 'Galavant,' More to Series |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 8, 2014 |accessdate=May 12, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509175159/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/abc-orders-how-get-away-702523 |archive-date=May 9, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The series features an ensemble cast with [[Alfred Enoch]], [[Jack Falahee]], [[Aja Naomi King]], [[Matt McGorry]], and [[Karla Souza]] as Keating's students, [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] and [[Liza Weil]] as her employees, and [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]] as a detective with the [[Philadelphia Police Department]], who is Annalise's lover. From the third season onward, [[Conrad Ricamora]] was promoted to the main cast after [[Recurring character|recurring]] heavily in the first two seasons.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/03/18/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-conrad-ricamora-series-regular-oliver/ |title=HTGAWM Promotes Conrad Ricamora to Series Regular in Season 3 |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |work=TVLine |date=March 18, 2016 |accessdate=March 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319211828/http://tvline.com/2016/03/18/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-conrad-ricamora-series-regular-oliver/ |archive-date=March 19, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nFor her performance, Davis has received critical acclaim; she became the first black woman to win the [[Primetime Emmy Award]] for [[Primetime Emmy Award for Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Lead Actress in a Drama Series]], also winning two [[Screen Actors Guild Award]]s for [[Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Performance by a Female Actor in a Drama Series]], and the [[NAACP Image Awards|Image Award]] for [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Actress in a Drama Series]]. Davis has also received nominations from the [[Golden Globe Awards]] for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress \u2013 Television Series Drama|Best Actress in a Television Series]], the [[Critics' Choice Television Awards|Critics' Choice Awards]] for [[Critics' Choice Television Award for Best Actress in a Drama Series|Best Actress in a Drama Series]], and the [[Television Critics Association]] at the [[TCA Awards]] for [[TCA Award for Individual Achievement in Drama|Individual Achievement in Drama]]. Other cast members have also received recognition for their performances, with Enoch and King receiving nominations from the [[NAACP Image Awards]] for [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actor in a Drama Series]] and [[NAACP Image Award for Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series|Outstanding Supporting Actress in a Drama Series]] at the [[46th NAACP Image Awards|2014 NAACP Image Awards ceremony]]. The series also received a [[GLAAD Media Award]] for Outstanding Drama Series.\n\nThe fifth season premiered on September 27, 2018. In May 2019, ABC renewed the series for a sixth and final season, which premiered on September 26, 2019.<ref name=\"S6FinalSeason\"/>\n\n==Series overview==\n{{main|List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes}}\n{{:List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes}}\n\n===Season 1===\n{{Main|How to Get Away with Murder (season 1)}}\nAnnalise Keating is a prominent [[Criminal defense lawyer|criminal defense attorney]] and law professor at Middleton University in [[Philadelphia]]. She selects five of her first year students to intern at her firm: Wes Gibbins, [[Connor Walsh (character)|Connor Walsh]], Michaela Pratt, Asher Millstone, and [[Laurel Castillo]] (The Keating 5). They work with Annalise's employees, Frank Delfino and [[Bonnie Winterbottom]], an associate lawyer. As the first season introduces occasional clients for Keating, it explores two related murders through both [[flashback (continuity)|flashback]] and [[flashforward]] sequences: Lila Stangard, mistress of Annalise's husband and a student at Middleton, and then Sam Keating, Annalise's husband, who was killed by Annalise's interns.\n\nThe first nine episodes alternate between the present-day timeline [[in medias res]], depicting Wes, Connor, Michaela, and Laurel covering up Sam's murder by disposing of his body, and flashbacks detailing the course of events [[foreshadowing|leading up]] to Sam's death, including Annalise's becoming involved in the Lila Stangard investigation, at Wes's urging, leading her to discover Sam's affair and creating suspicion that he killed Lila. The final six episodes explore Annalise's attempt to help her interns cover up Sam's murder and legally implicate Sam in Lila's death, and flashbacks to Lila's final moments before her murder.\n\n===Season 2===\n{{Main|How to Get Away with Murder (season 2)}}\nThe first nine episodes focus on Annalise's defense of Caleb and Catherine Hapstall, who were accused of torturing and murdering their adoptive parents. Wes, in the meantime, teams up with Rebecca's foster brother to try and find Rebecca. Connor struggles with his relationship with Oliver, while Asher works with A.D.A. Emily Sinclair, in order to protect his secrets. In the mid-season finale, Sinclair is murdered, and Annalise helps cover it up, at the expense of her being shot in the stomach by Wes.\n\nThe second part of the season focuses on Wes's investigation of his mother's suicide 10 years ago; flashbacks reveal Annalise's involvement with Wes's mother's suicide. The season ends with Annalise's finding out that Frank was responsible for the car crash that killed her baby, and Annalise sending him away. Michaela and Asher hook up, and Wes meets with his biological father right before the latter is shot dead by an unknown shooter.\n\n===Season 3===\n{{Main|How to Get Away with Murder (season 3)}}\nIn the aftermath of Wallace Mahoney's death, all five of the students attempt to move on. A new mystery arises around the burning down of Annalise's house and who was found dead inside. The events leading up to it involve Annalise's starting a free legal clinic and struggling with alcoholism. Oliver starts working for Annalise, and he leaves Connor when becoming disgusted with himself for rejecting Connor's [[Stanford]] acceptance. Michaela and Asher's relationship starts to progress, as does Wes and Laurel's, and Frank starts working to atone for the death of Annalise's child. Ultimately, it is revealed that it was Wes who died, and that he was killed before the fire. Annalise is arrested for Wes's death. Frank attempts to help Annalise by confessing to killing Wes. It is further revealed that Wes's death was commissioned by Laurel's father, who disapproved of their relationship.\n\n===Season 4===\n{{main|How to Get Away with Murder (season 4)}}\nIn the fourth season, Annalise works with a therapist, Dr. Isaac Roa, to see through her recovery from alcoholism. She initially cuts ties with Bonnie (who moves to the [[District Attorney of Philadelphia|DA's office]] as an [[assistant district attorney]] reporting to DA Todd Denver) and the interns, gets a woman with a long rap sheet freed from jail, and then commits to a major [[class action]] against the state for [[miscarriage of justice|miscarriages of justice]] caused by an underfunded [[public defender]]'s office. Laurel deduces that her father, Jorge Castillo, is responsible for Wes's murder and hatches a scheme to steal incriminating evidence from his law firm with the help of Michaela, Oliver, Frank, and Asher. During the data heist, their classmate Simon (Behzad Dabu) accidentally shoots himself with Laurel's gun, leading to Asher's arrest, and Laurel goes into premature labor after being accidentally struck by Frank. Annalise successfully saves the baby. However, Jorge claims custody of his grandchild by submitting evidence of Laurel's past addictions and history of mental illness to a judge. Laurel's mother arrives unexpectedly to \"help\" Laurel fight against her father, and Frank and Bonnie uncover a mysterious link between Laurel's mother and both Wes and his killer, Dominic. Meanwhile, Annalise searches for alternative ways to win her class action lawsuit. On January 3, 2018, a crossover with ''[[Scandal (TV series)|Scandal]]'' was announced which aired on March 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/01/scandal-how-to-get-away-with-murder-crossover-shonda-rhimes-kerry-washington-viola-davis-htgawm-creator-qa-1202234080/ |title='Scandal'/'How To Get Away With Murder' Crossover: Get Details On Big Shondaland Event From 'HTGAWM' Creator \u2013 Q&A |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=January 3, 2018 |work=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=January 3, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180103215340/http://deadline.com/2018/01/scandal-how-to-get-away-with-murder-crossover-shonda-rhimes-kerry-washington-viola-davis-htgawm-creator-qa-1202234080/ |archive-date=January 3, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Season 5===\n{{main|How to Get Away with Murder (season 5)}}\nOn May 11, 2018, ABC renewed the series for a fifth season, which premiered on September 27, 2018.<ref name=\"season5renewal\"/>\n\nAfter Annalise Keating's class-action victory in the Supreme Court, she and her associates seek to start a new chapter in their lives. Annalise starts working at Caplan & Gold so she can use their resources for her class-action cases, while also working back at Middleton. Michaela Pratt, Connor Walsh, Asher Millstone and Laurel Castillo start their third year at law school, and a new student, Gabriel Maddox joins the group on Annalise's class. Meanwhile, Frank tries to find out the real reason Maddox came to Middleton in the first place, and Asher joins Bonnie at the DA's office as he gets an intership there. At the same time, Connor and Oliver Hampton also start planning their wedding, which is seen through new flashforwards that reveal a new murder committed.\n\n===Season 6===\n{{main|How to Get Away with Murder (season 6)}}\nThe sixth and final season of the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] American [[television drama]] series ''How to Get Away with Murder'' was ordered in May 2019 by ABC.<ref name=\"Season 6 renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-6-abc-1202607397/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' Renewed For Season 6 By ABC|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=May 10, 2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510165732/https://deadline.com/2019/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-6-abc-1202607397/|archive-date=May 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that year, in July, it was announced the sixth season would be the last.<ref name=\"S6FinalSeason\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/video/how-to-get-away-with-murder-end-season-6-abc/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' To End With Season 6 On ABC|website=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|date=July 11, 2019|accessdate=July 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711152428/https://deadline.com/video/how-to-get-away-with-murder-end-season-6-abc/|archive-date=July 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Season 6 premiered on September 26, 2019.\n\n==Cast and characters==\n<!---Per credit order. Except Viola Davis, the original cast members are credited in alphabetical order. Add new cast members to the end of the list.--->\n{{main|List of How to Get Away with Murder characters}}\n* [[Viola Davis]] as [[Annalise Keating]], a high-profile criminal defense attorney and law professor at Middleton University, whose life has been filled with trauma\n* [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]] as Nate Lahey, a Philadelphia police detective who at the start of the series is having an affair with Annalise\n* [[Alfred Enoch]] as Wes Gibbins (main seasons 1\u20133; guest seasons 4 and 6), a law student and a member of Annalise's group of favored students{{Snd}}the so-called Keating 5{{Snd}}and about whom she feels especially protective\n* [[Jack Falahee]] as [[Connor Walsh (character)|Connor Walsh]], a cunning and hard-working member of the Keating 5 whose confident and seductive \"alpha gay\" exterior obscures his insecurities\n* [[Katie Findlay]] as Rebecca Sutter (main season 1; guest season 2), Wes' neighbor\n* [[Aja Naomi King]] as Michaela Pratt, a high-flying overachiever and a member of the Keating 5 who is determined to make a success of her life\n* [[Matt McGorry]] as Asher Millstone, a member of the Keating 5 from a privileged [[White Anglo Saxon Protestant|WASP]] background who feels left out of the group\n* [[Karla Souza]] as Laurel Castillo (main seasons 1\u20135; guest season 6), a resourceful Keating 5 member whose distant, wealthy father is the kingpin of an [[organized crime]] empire\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] as Frank Delfino, Annalise's fixer and private detective\n* [[Liza Weil]] as [[Bonnie Winterbottom]], Annalise's associate and right-hand woman, whose childhood and early adulthood were filled with horrifying events\n* [[Conrad Ricamora]] as Oliver Hampton (main seasons 3\u20136; recurring seasons 1\u20132), a talented computer hacker who Connor seduces and later married\n* [[Rome Flynn]] as Gabriel Maddox (main season 5\u20136; guest season 4), a mysterious young man and aspiring civil rights lawyer who arrives at Middleton University eager to investigate Annalise and the Keating 5\n* [[Amirah Vann]] as Tegan Price (main seasons 5\u20136; recurring season 4), a powerful attorney at Caplan & Gold, the firm representing Laurel's father\n* [[Timothy Hutton]] as Emmett Crawford (main season 5), a managing partner at Caplan & Gold who develops an attraction towards Annalise\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\n[[File:Shonda Rhimes 2008 cropped and retouched.jpg|thumb|left|165px|[[Shonda Rhimes]], co-executive producer of ''How to Get Away with Murder'']]\nOn August 19, 2013, ABC bought from Shondaland Productions the original concept, produced by [[Shonda Rhimes]] and [[Betsy Beers]]. The script for the pilot episode was written by ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' supervising producer [[Peter Nowalk]].<ref name=\"Writer\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/08/abc-buys-legal-thriller-from-shondaland-greys-anatomy-writer/ |title=ABC Buys Legal Thriller From Shondaland & 'Grey's Anatomy' Writer |website=Deadline Hollywood |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=August 19, 2013 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520160639/http://www.deadline.com/2013/08/abc-buys-legal-thriller-from-shondaland-greys-anatomy-writer/ |archive-date=May 20, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> ABC ordered the pilot on December 19, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2013/12/sea-of-fire-shondalands-how-to-get-away-with-murder-get-abc-pilot-orders/ |title='Sea Of Fire' & Shondaland's 'How To Get Away With Murder' Get ABC Pilot Orders |work=Deadline Hollywood |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=December 19, 2013 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140423072715/http://www.deadline.com/2013/12/sea-of-fire-shondalands-how-to-get-away-with-murder-get-abc-pilot-orders/ |archive-date=April 23, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On May 8, 2014, ABC picked up the pilot to series<ref>{{cite web |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/05/abc-picks-up-shonda-rhimes-how-to-get-away-with-murder-anthony-anderson-american-crime/ |title=ABC New Series Pickups: 'Selfie', 'Forever', Galavant', 'Whispers', 'How To Get Away With Murder', 'American Crime', 'Black-ish', Jeff Lowell Comedy |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=May 8, 2014 |accessdate=May 12, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713050410/http://www.deadline.com/2014/05/abc-picks-up-shonda-rhimes-how-to-get-away-with-murder-anthony-anderson-american-crime/ |archive-date=July 13, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> for the 2014\u201315 television season.<ref>{{cite web |first=Cynthia |last=Littleton |url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/abc-orders-viola-davis-drama-how-to-get-away-with-murder-1201176035/ |title=ABC Orders 'Marvel's Agent Carter,' 4 Other Dramas and 4 Comedies |website=Variety |date=May 8, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140509175531/http://variety.com/2014/tv/news/abc-orders-viola-davis-drama-how-to-get-away-with-murder-1201176035/ |archive-date=May 9, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> At the [[Television Critics Association]] Press Tour in July 2014, it was announced that ''How to Get Away with Murder'' would be a limited series with only 15 or 16 episodes per season.<ref>{{cite web |website=[[TV Guide]] |date=July 15, 2014 |url=https://twitter.com/TVGuide/status/489095092636876801 |title=#Scandal will do a full 22-episode season, while #HowToGetAwayWithMurder will only do 15 or 16 episodes #TCA14 |accessdate=July 16, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140817063831/https://twitter.com/TVGuide/status/489095092636876801 |archive-date=August 17, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The smaller size of episode count stems from the deal for the series star Viola Davis.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2014/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-blackish-full-season-1-orders-abc-848758/ |title='How To Get Away With Murder' & 'Black-Ish': Full-Season Orders At ABC |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=October 9, 2014 |accessdate=November 1, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024064124/http://deadline.com/2014/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-blackish-full-season-1-orders-abc-848758/ |archive-date=October 24, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On October 9, 2014, ABC picked up the series for a full season of 15 episodes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/10/09/how-to-get-away-with-murder-and-black-ish-get-full-season-orders-at-abc/312767/ |title='How to Get Away With Murder' and 'black-sh'Get Full Season Orders at ABC |website=TV by the Numbers |last=Kondolojy |first=Amanda |date=October 9, 2014 |accessdate=October 24, 2014 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024083749/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/10/09/how-to-get-away-with-murder-and-black-ish-get-full-season-orders-at-abc/312767/ |archivedate=October 24, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe series was renewed for a second season on May 7, 2015, by ABC.<ref name=\"renewal\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/abc-forever-cristela-resurrection-cancelled-1201490485/ |title=ABC Cancels 'Forever,' 'Cristela,' 'Resurrection' & 'The Taste' |last=Wagmeister |first=Elizabeth |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=May 7, 2015 |accessdate=May 8, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509023328/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/abc-forever-cristela-resurrection-cancelled-1201490485/ |archive-date=May 9, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> The series was effectively confirmed as earning a second-season renewal for the 2015\u201316 season via a promo succeeding the first-season finale and an earlier statement by Viola Davis also confirming the renewal at the close of shooting for the first season.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-renewed-778216 |title=How to Get Away With Murder' Promo Plugs Season 2 Renewal |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=February 26, 2015 |accessdate=July 14, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704235622/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-renewed-778216 |archive-date=July 4, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-2-renewal-viola-davis-tweet-htgawm-1201419385/ |title='How to Get Away With Murder': Viola Davis Says Season 2 Is a Go |last=Wagmeister |first=Elizabeth |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |date=January 30, 2015 |accessdate=July 14, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150703090626/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-2-renewal-viola-davis-tweet-htgawm-1201419385/ |archive-date=July 3, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> It would contain 15 episodes, like the previous season.<ref name=\"episode count\">{{cite web |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/abc-renewals-cancellations-fall-2015/ |title=ABC Renews Once, Castle and More; Cancels Forever, Cristela |website=[[TVGuide]] |last=Ngyuen |first=Hanh |date=May 7, 2015 |accessdate=May 8, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150510164337/http://www.tvguide.com/news/abc-renewals-cancellations-fall-2015/ |archive-date=May 10, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> Production began on May 21, 2015, with [[Shonda Rhimes]] announcing on [[Twitter]] that [[Peter Nowalk]] and his writers were in full swing mapping the second season.<ref name=\"Rhimes\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/shondarhimes/status/601418253630459904 |title=Spending today in both Writers Rooms (#GreysAnatomy and #Scandal) and @petenowa has begun the #HTGAWM Room! Next season is in full swing!! |website=Twitter |last=Rhimes |first=Shonda |date=May 21, 2015 |accessdate=July 15, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312172048/https://twitter.com/shondarhimes/status/601418253630459904 |archive-date=March 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The table read for the premiere occurred on July 14, 2015,<ref name=\"Davis\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/violadavis/status/621077025109839872/photo/1 |title=Season 2 read thru BABY!!! #HTGAWM |website=Twitter |last=Davis |first=Viola |date=July 14, 2015 |accessdate=July 15, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160306004537/https://twitter.com/violadavis/status/621077025109839872/photo/1 |archive-date=March 6, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> with the title of the episode being revealed at the same time.<ref name=\"premiere title\">{{cite web |url=https://www.facebook.com/HowToGetAwayWithMurder/photos/a.658480037557397.1073741829.611490952256306/885208034884595/?type=1&theater |title=It's all happening!!! #HTGAWM Season 2 Episode 1 Table Read!!! |website=[[Facebook]] |date=July 14, 2015 |accessdate=July 15, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312172048/https://www.facebook.com/HowToGetAwayWithMurder/photos/a.658480037557397.1073741829.611490952256306/885208034884595/?type=1&theater |archive-date=March 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' reported on July 23, 2015, that the identity of Rebecca's killer would be revealed in the season premiere.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/23/how-get-away-murder-rebecca-killer-season-2-premiere |title=How to Get Away with Murder to reveal Rebecca's killer sooner than expected |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=July 23, 2015 |accessdate=August 1, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150803053336/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/23/how-get-away-murder-rebecca-killer-season-2-premiere |archive-date=August 3, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> A promotional poster was released over a month before the season premiere, on August 17, 2015.\n\nThe series was renewed for a third season on March 3, 2016, along with several other series by ABC.<ref name=\"renewed\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/03/03/abc-renewed-series-2016-greys-anatomy-shield/ |title=Grey's Anatomy, Scandal, S.H.I.E.L.D. and 8 Other Shows Renewed at ABC |website=TVLine |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |date=March 3, 2016 |accessdate=March 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612061115/http://tvline.com/2016/03/03/abc-renewed-series-2016-greys-anatomy-shield/ |archive-date=June 12, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> It was announced that the third season would premiere on September 22, 2016.<ref name=\"premiere date\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/06/28/abc-premiere-dates-fall-2016-greys-anatomy-once-upon-a-time/ |title=ABC Sets Fall Premiere Dates for Grey's, Once, Kiefer's POTUS Drama and More |website=[[TVLine]] |last=Mitovich |first=Matt Webb |date=June 28, 2016 |accessdate=June 28, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160629044225/http://tvline.com/2016/06/28/abc-premiere-dates-fall-2016-greys-anatomy-once-upon-a-time/ |archive-date=June 29, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Production began on May 27, 2016, when showrunner [[Peter Nowalk]] announced on Twitter that the writer staff were in full swing mapping and writing the third season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/petenowalk/status/736307875643981825 |title=Writing the Season 3 premiere outline. How the f did we get so far? Thank you my little murderers #HTGAWM |website=Twitter |last=Nowalk |first=Peter |date=May 27, 2016 |accessdate=July 20, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312172617/https://twitter.com/petenowalk/status/736307875643981825 |archive-date=March 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The table read for the premiere happened on July 6, 2016,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BHf4Se9gGSB/ |title=First read through of season 3 #htgawm #gagging |website=[[Instagram]] |last=Nowalk |first=Peter |date=July 6, 2016 |accessdate=July 20, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312172617/https://www.instagram.com/p/BHf4Se9gGSB/ |archive-date=March 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> with filming starting a week later.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BHvZmt3Aygk/ |title=First shoot day of Season 3\ufe0f\u20e3 #HTGAWM |website=Instagram |last=Nowalk |first=Peter |date=July 12, 2016 |accessdate=July 20, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312172617/https://www.instagram.com/p/BHvZmt3Aygk/ |archive-date=March 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> A promotional poster showcasing Viola Davis as Annalise Keating, was released on August 9, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://zap2it.com/2016/08/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-poster-annalise-smiles/ |title='HTGAWM' exclusive: What put that Mona Lisa smile on Annalise's face? |website=Zap2It |last=Macdonald |first=Lindsay |date=August 9, 2016 |accessdate=August 10, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160810164813/http://zap2it.com/2016/08/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-poster-annalise-smiles/ |archive-date=August 10, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> ABC released a promo for the third season on August 29, 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/29/how-get-away-murder-season-3-promo |title=How to Get Away with Murder: Exclusive promo unveils killer new season 3 mystery |website=Entertainment Weekly |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=August 29, 2016 |accessdate=August 29, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160830173601/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/29/how-get-away-murder-season-3-promo |archive-date=August 30, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe series was renewed for a fourth season on February 10, 2017, by ABC.<ref name=\"season4renewal\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2017/02/10/greys-anatomy-renewed-scandal-htgawm-renewals/ |title=Grey's Anatomy, Scandal and HTGAWM Renewed for 2017-18 Season |last=Swift |first=Andy |work=[[TVLine]] |date=February 10, 2017 |accessdate=February 11, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211000238/http://tvline.com/2017/02/10/greys-anatomy-renewed-scandal-htgawm-renewals/ |archive-date=February 11, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe series was renewed for a fifth season on May 11, 2018, by ABC,<ref name=\"season5renewal\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2018/05/11/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-5-abc/ |title=How to Get Away With Murder Renewed for Season 5 at ABC |last=Iannucci |first=Rebecca |work=[[TVLine]] |date=May 11, 2018 |accessdate=May 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180512044143/http://tvline.com/2018/05/11/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-5-abc/ |archive-date=May 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> which premiered on September 27, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2018/07/24/abc-premiere-dates-fall-2018-greys-anatomy-the-conners/ |title=ABC Fall Premiere Dates: XL Grey's, Nathan Fillion's Rookie, The Conners (Minus Roseanne) and More |last=Swift |first=Andy |work=[[TVLine]] |date=July 24, 2018 |accessdate=July 24, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724212649/https://tvline.com/2018/07/24/abc-premiere-dates-fall-2018-greys-anatomy-the-conners/ |archive-date=July 24, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn May 10, 2019, the series was renewed for a sixth season which premiered on September 26, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-6-abc-1202607397/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' Renewed For Season 6 By ABC|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=May 10, 2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510165732/https://deadline.com/2019/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-6-abc-1202607397/|archive-date=May 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/07/abc-fall-premiere-dates-2019-1202641119/|title=ABC Fall Premiere Dates: 'The Conners', 'Black-ish' & Spinoff, Cobie Smulders' 'Stumptown', Final 'Modern Family' Season & More|last=Pedersen|first=Erik|date=July 2, 2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702185325/https://deadline.com/2019/07/abc-fall-premiere-dates-2019-1202641119/|archive-date=July 2, 2019|accessdate=July 2, 2019}}</ref> On July 11, 2019, it was reported that the sixth season will be the final season.<ref name=\"S6FinalSeason\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/video/how-to-get-away-with-murder-end-season-6-abc/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' To End With Season 6 On ABC|website=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|date=July 11, 2019|accessdate=July 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711152428/https://deadline.com/video/how-to-get-away-with-murder-end-season-6-abc/|archive-date=July 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Writing===\nIn an interview with ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'', showrunner [[Peter Nowalk]] talked about what would happen in the third season regarding Frank's disappearance; he commented: \"Yes, I can see the three-piece suits and the hair product all falling apart. It's more what Frank feels about himself\". When talking about the trust between Annalise and Frank, Nowalk said: \"...Frank has two choices: To run away and hope she never catches him, just to cut bait; or he can try to win his way back. That's a long road\".<ref name=\"EW recap\" /> [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] commented on Frank's whereabouts as he said to ''Entertainment Weekly'' \"I think he's hiding, and I think he's alone. If he does have a lifeline, I don't think it's Laurel\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/17/how-get-away-murder-charlie-weber-frank-spoilers |title=How to Get Away with Murder star Charlie Weber on heartbreaking Frank twist |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=March 17, 2016 |accessdate=March 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319044952/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/17/how-get-away-murder-charlie-weber-frank-spoilers |archive-date=March 19, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nRegarding Laurel, Nowalk said that Laurel's backstory with her family would be explored in the upcoming season, \"I feel like it's very present. The promise of our show is that we won't dangle things out too long. The likelihood is yes. We've raised that question too many times not to answer it sooner than later\". Michaela's backstory would also be explored as Nowalk said \"We have so much to explore with her. Aja is so talented. I'm just excited to really delve into her personal life next year\".<ref name=\"EW recap\">{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/17/how-get-away-murder-finale-death-season-3-spoilers |title=How to Get Away with Murder postmortem: Who killed the latest victim? |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |last=Abrams |first=Natalie |date=March 17, 2016 |accessdate=March 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160319044808/http://www.ew.com/article/2016/03/17/how-get-away-murder-finale-death-season-3-spoilers |archive-date=March 19, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Talking to ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'', Nowalk stated that the series would explore both [[Annalise Keating|Annalise]] and Nate's relationship and both their families.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-creator-876452 |title='How to Get Away With Murder' Creator Explains Killer Finale Twists |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Dowling |first=Amber |date=March 17, 2016 |accessdate=March 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160320224939/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-creator-876452 |archive-date=March 20, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[File:HTGAWMCastS4.png|right|thumb|320px|Cast members of season 4, from left to right: [[Matt McGorry]], [[Aja Naomi King]], [[Karla Souza]], [[Conrad Ricamora]], [[Jack Falahee]], [[Viola Davis]], [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]], [[Liza Weil]], and [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]]]]\n\n===Casting===\nOn January 21, 2014, [[Matt McGorry]] was the first to be announced as a regular cast member, playing a law student.<ref name=\"Matt McGorry\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/01/matt-mcgorry-cast-in-abc-murder-pilot-mike-colter-in-tnts-agent-x/ |title=Matt McGorry Cast In ABC 'Murder' Pilot, Mike Colter In TNT's 'Agent X' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=January 31, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140514195455/http://www.deadline.com/2014/01/matt-mcgorry-cast-in-abc-murder-pilot-mike-colter-in-tnts-agent-x/ |archive-date=May 14, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Throughout February and March 2014, other roles were announced as cast: [[Aja Naomi King]],<ref name=\"Aja Naomi King\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/02/aja-naomi-king-cast-in-abc-pilot-murder-arden-myrin-in-nbcs-bad-judge/ |title=Aja Naomi King Cast In ABC Pilot 'Murder'; Arden Myrin in NBC's 'Bad Judge' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=February 6, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140307063959/http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/aja-naomi-king-cast-in-abc-pilot-murder-arden-myrin-in-nbcs-bad-judge/ |archive-date=March 7, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Jack Falahee]],<ref name=\"Alfred Enoch, Jack Falahee, Karla Souza\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/02/christina-chang-joins-abc-pilot-sea-of-fire-alfred-enoch-karla-kouza-in-murder/ |title=UPDATE: Jeffrey Nordling & Christina Chang In ABC's 'Sea Of Fire', Trio Cast In 'Murder' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=February 12, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505234002/http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/christina-chang-joins-abc-pilot-sea-of-fire-alfred-enoch-karla-kouza-in-murder/ |archive-date=May 5, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"Alfred Enoch, Karla Souza\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/11/17/alfred-enoch-leaving-how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-wes-dead/ |title=How to Get Away With Murder Victim Dishes Character's 'Bleak' Ending, Autopsy Makeup, Bond With Annalise |last=Slezak |first=Michael |work=TVLine |date=November 17, 2016 |accessdate=November 18, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118164440/http://tvline.com/2016/11/17/alfred-enoch-leaving-how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-wes-dead/ |archive-date=November 18, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Alfred Enoch]]<ref name=\"Alfred Enoch, Jack Falahee, Karla Souza\"/> and [[Karla Souza]]<ref name=\"Alfred Enoch, Jack Falahee, Karla Souza\"/> as law students; [[Katie Findlay]] as a drug-dealing student;<ref name=\"Katie Findlay\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/03/katie-findlay-joins-how-to-get-away-utkarsh-ambudkar-in-love-is-relative/ |title=Katie Findlay Joins 'How To Get Away', Utkarsh Ambudkar In 'Love Is Relative' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 1, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520160721/http://www.deadline.com/2014/03/katie-findlay-joins-how-to-get-away-utkarsh-ambudkar-in-love-is-relative/ |archive-date=May 20, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] as a law associate to Professor Keating;<ref name=\"Charlie Weber\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/02/charlie-weber-cast-in-how-to-get-away-the-flash-gets-mother/ |title=Charlie Weber Cast In 'How To Get Away'; 'The Flash' Gets Mother |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=February 24, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429034659/http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/charlie-weber-cast-in-how-to-get-away-the-flash-gets-mother/ |archive-date=April 29, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]] as Professor Keating's extra-marital love interest;<ref name=\"Billy Brown\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/03/aimee-garcia-cbs-pilot-red-zone-billy-brown-abc-how-to-get-away/ |title=Aimee Garcia Cast In CBS Pilot 'Red Zone'; Billy Brown In ABC's 'How To Get Away' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 2, 2014 |accessdate=May 20, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140520160511/http://www.deadline.com/2014/03/aimee-garcia-cbs-pilot-red-zone-billy-brown-abc-how-to-get-away/ |archive-date=May 20, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> veteran actor and producer [[Tom Verica]] as Professor Keating's husband;<ref name=\"Tom Verica\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/03/tom-verica-cast-in-abc-pilot-how-to-get-away-morgan-spector-in-nbcs-coercion/ |title=Tom Verica Cast In ABC Pilot 'How To Get Away'; Morgan Spector In NBC's 'Coercion' |last=The Deadline Team |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=March 10, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140420064707/http://www.deadline.com/2014/03/tom-verica-cast-in-abc-pilot-how-to-get-away-morgan-spector-in-nbcs-coercion/ |archive-date=April 20, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[Liza Weil]] as one of the professor's two associates.<ref name= \"Liza Weil\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/02/liza-weil-cast-in-abc-pilot-how-to-get-away-stephen-hagan-in-cws-identity/ |title=Liza Weil Cast In ABC Pilot 'How To Get Away', Stephen Hagan In CW's 'Identity' |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=February 27, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504055704/http://www.deadline.com/2014/02/liza-weil-cast-in-abc-pilot-how-to-get-away-stephen-hagan-in-cws-identity/ |archive-date=May 4, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn February 25, 2014, it was announced that Shonda Rhimes had cast [[Viola Davis]] in the series' leading role of Professor Annalise Keating.<ref>{{cite web |first=Natalie |last=Abrams |url=https://www.tvguide.com/news/abc-viola-davis-how-get-murder-pilot-1078211.aspx |title=Viola Davis Lands Lead in ABC Pilot How to Get Away With Murder |work=TV Guide |date=February 25, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140410232943/http://www.tvguide.com/News/ABC-Viola-Davis-How-Get-Murder-Pilot-1078211.aspx |archive-date=April 10, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 11, 2014, it was announced that ''[[Orange is the New Black]]'' alum [[Alysia Reiner]] had joined the cast as a prosecutor who would be going up against Annalise.<ref name=\"Vick\">{{cite web |url=http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/how_to_get_away_with_murder_casts_orange_is_the_new_black_alysia_reiner-2014-08 |title='How to Get Away with Murder' casts 'Orange is the New Black' alum Alysia Reiner |work=Zap2It |last=Vick |first=Megan |date=August 11, 2014 |accessdate=November 28, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141128074750/http://www.zap2it.com/blogs/how_to_get_away_with_murder_casts_orange_is_the_new_black_alysia_reiner-2014-08 |archive-date=November 28, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On November 4, 2014, it was announced that Oscar winner [[Marcia Gay Harden]] had joined the cast in the second half of the first season for a recurring role.<ref name=\"Marcia Gay Harden\">{{cite web |last1=Friedlander |first1=Whitney |title=Marcia Gay Harden Joins 'How to Get Away with Murder' |url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/news/marcia-gay-harden-how-to-get-away-with-murder-1201347849/ |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Business Media]] |date=November 4, 2014 |accessdate=November 12, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107154030/http://variety.com/2014/tv/news/marcia-gay-harden-how-to-get-away-with-murder-1201347849/ |archive-date=November 7, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> On December 15, 2014, it was announced that Oscar nominee and Emmy winner [[Cicely Tyson]] would appear in an episode in the second half of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-enlists-757903 |title='How to Get Away With Murder' Enlists Cicely Tyson |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |accessdate=December 15, 2014 |date=December 15, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150206051827/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-enlists-757903 |archive-date=February 6, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Famke Janssen by Gage Skidmore (2) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|150px|In 2015, [[Famke Janssen]] joined the cast as Defense Attorney Eve Rothlo.]]\nIt was announced on July 14, 2015, that the second season would introduce several new characters, including a family consisting of Caleb, Catherine and Helena Hapstall.<ref name=\"hapstall\">{{cite web |url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/675753/spoiler-chat-scoop-on-vampire-diaries-walking-dead-empire-arrow-and-more |title=Spoiler Chat: Scoop on Vampire Diaries, Walking Dead, Empire, Arrow and More! |work=[[E! Online]] |last=Dos Santos |first=Kristin |date=July 14, 2015 |accessdate=July 16, 2015}}</ref> [[Katie Findlay]] would return to play the character Rebecca Sutter, who was killed in the first-season finale.<ref name=\"findlay\">{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/katedangerfield/status/623318048812892161 |title=I work with the nicest people on the planet. @HowToGetAwayABC |work=Twitter |last=Findlay |first=Katie |date=July 20, 2015 |accessdate=August 1, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312172048/https://twitter.com/katedangerfield/status/623318048812892161 |archive-date=March 12, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On July 22, 2015, it was announced that Kendrick Sampson, known from ''[[The Vampire Diaries (TV series)|The Vampire Diaries]]'' would join the cast in the second season and be introduced in the season premiere.<ref name=\"Sampson\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/07/kendrick-sampson-cast-how-to-get-away-with-murder-viola-davis-abc-1201483183/ |title=Kendrick Sampson Joins 'How To Get Away With Murder' |work=Deadline Hollywood |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=July 22, 2015 |accessdate=August 1, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150801050150/https://deadline.com/2015/07/kendrick-sampson-cast-how-to-get-away-with-murder-viola-davis-abc-1201483183/ |archive-date=August 1, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> On July 31, 2015, it was announced that [[Famke Janssen]] had joined the cast as a brilliant, revered defense attorney for a multi-episode arc and would first appear in the season premiere.<ref name=\"Janssen\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2015/07/31/famke-janssen-htgawm-season-2-how-to-get-away-with-murder/ |title=How to Get Away With Murder Season 2: X-Men's Famke Janssen Lands Arc |work=TVLine |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |date=July 31, 2015 |accessdate=August 1, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150801152147/http://tvline.com/2015/07/31/famke-janssen-htgawm-season-2-how-to-get-away-with-murder/ |archive-date=August 1, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[Matt Cohen (actor)|Matt Cohen]] was announced on August 11, 2015, to recur in the second season as Levi Wescott, who is described as a sexy, edgy working class guy.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2015/08/matt-cohen-cast-how-to-get-away-with-murder-abc-shonda-rhimes-1201497079/ |title=Matt Cohen Joins 'How To Get Away With Murder |work=Deadline Hollywood |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=August 11, 2015 |accessdate=August 11, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150811232807/http://deadline.com/2015/08/matt-cohen-cast-how-to-get-away-with-murder-abc-shonda-rhimes-1201497079/ |archive-date=August 11, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 31, 2015, ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported that [[Amy Okuda]] would play a recurring role, but details on Okuda's part were being kept under wraps.<ref name=\"okuda\">{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/how-to-get-away-with-murder-adds-new-character-for-season-2-exclusive-1201582076/ |title='How to Get Away With Murder' Adds New Character for Season 2 (EXCLUSIVE) |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |last=Wagmeister |first=Elizabeth |date=August 31, 2015 |accessdate=September 1, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150831230403/http://variety.com/2015/tv/news/how-to-get-away-with-murder-adds-new-character-for-season-2-exclusive-1201582076/ |archive-date=August 31, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Sherri Saum]] was announced to have been cast as a guest star on September 30, 2015.<ref name=\"saum\">{{cite web |url=https://www.thewrap.com/how-to-get-away-with-murder-casts-the-fosters-star-sherri-saum-in-guest-role/ |title='How to Get Away With Murder' Casts 'The Fosters' Star Sherri Saum in Guest Role |work=[[TheWrap]] |date=September 30, 2015 |accessdate=October 4, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151003232532/http://www.thewrap.com/how-to-get-away-with-murder-casts-the-fosters-star-sherri-saum-in-guest-role/ |archive-date=October 3, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> On January 14, 2016, it was announced that [[Wilson Bethel]], [[Adam Arkin]], and [[Roxanne Hart]] would be joining the series to play the Mahoney family. Bethel would play Charles Mahoney, the Ivy League-educated son, with Arkin playing his father Wallace and Hart playing his mother Sylvia.<ref name=\"mahoney\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/01/14/how-to-get-away-with-murder-wilson-bethel-adam-arkin-cast/ |title=How to Get Away With Murder Casts Wilson Bethel, Adam Arkin for 'Big' Arc |work=TVLine |last=Slezak |first=Michael |date=January 14, 2016 |accessdate=January 15, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115094950/http://tvline.com/2016/01/14/how-to-get-away-with-murder-wilson-bethel-adam-arkin-cast/ |archive-date=January 15, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter the second-season finale, it was announced that ''[[Dexter (TV series)|Dexter]]'' alum [[Lauren V\u00e9lez]] had joined the cast in a recurring role as the President of Middleton University. The role was described as \"self-assured, friendly, warm and diplomatic\".<ref name=\"principal\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/07/20/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-cast-lauren-velez-htgawm/ |title=HTGAWM Taps Dexter Alum To Recur as 'President' in Season 3 |work=TVLine |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |date=July 20, 2016 |accessdate=July 20, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721112347/http://tvline.com/2016/07/20/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-cast-lauren-velez-htgawm/ |archive-date=July 21, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> On August 6, 2016, it was announced that [[Esai Morales]] and [[Amy Madigan]] had joined the cast as guest stars for the third season.<ref name=\"esai\">{{cite web |url=http://tvline.com/2016/08/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-esai-morales-cast/ |title=HTGAWM Books NYPD Blue, Grey's Alums for Season 3 Guest Stints |work=[[TVLine]] |last=Ausiello |first=Michael |date=August 5, 2016 |accessdate=August 6, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160806152707/http://tvline.com/2016/08/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-3-esai-morales-cast/ |archive-date=August 6, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Deadline Hollywood|Deadline]]'' announced on August 31, 2016, that [[Mary J. Blige]] had landed a guest role in the third season.<ref name=\"blige\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2016/08/mary-j-blige-guest-star-how-to-get-away-with-murder-viola-davis-shondaland-abc-1201810862/ |title=Mary J. Blige To Guest Star In 'How To Get Away With Murder' |work=Deadline Hollywood |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=August 31, 2016 |accessdate=August 31, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160901101755/http://deadline.com/2016/08/mary-j-blige-guest-star-how-to-get-away-with-murder-viola-davis-shondaland-abc-1201810862/ |archive-date=September 1, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn June 7, 2018, it was announced that [[Rome Flynn]], who made a cameo appearance as Gabriel Maddox at the end of the fourth-season finale, was promoted to regular status for the upcoming fifth season.<ref name=\"Flynn\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/06/how-to-get-away-with-murder-rome-flynn-upped-series-regular-season-5-abc-drama-gabriel-maddox-1202405972/ |title='How To Get Away With Murder': Rome Flynn Upped To Series Regular For Season 5 |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=June 7, 2018 |work=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=June 10, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180608034711/https://deadline.com/2018/06/how-to-get-away-with-murder-rome-flynn-upped-series-regular-season-5-abc-drama-gabriel-maddox-1202405972/ |archive-date=June 8, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On July 18, it was reported that [[Amirah Vann]], who recurred as Tegan Price during the fourth season, would also join the regular cast for the fifth season.<ref name=\"Vann\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/how-to-get-away-with-murder-amirah-vann-promoted-series-regular-season-5-1202428331/ |title='How To Get Away With Murder': Amirah Vann Upped To Series Regular For Season 5 |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=July 18, 2018 |work=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=July 18, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180718192338/https://deadline.com/2018/07/how-to-get-away-with-murder-amirah-vann-promoted-series-regular-season-5-1202428331/ |archive-date=July 18, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> On July 30, 2018, it was announced that [[Timothy Hutton]] had joined the main cast for the fifth season.<ref name=\"Hutton\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/how-to-get-away-with-murder-timothy-hutton-series-regular-season-5-1202435327/ |title='How To Get Away With Murder': Timothy Hutton Joins As Series Regular In Season 5 |last=Petski |first=Denise |date=July 30, 2018 |work=Deadline Hollywood |accessdate=July 30, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180730205734/https://deadline.com/2018/07/how-to-get-away-with-murder-timothy-hutton-series-regular-season-5-1202435327/ |archive-date=July 30, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nThe pilot episode was filmed in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], at the [[University of Southern California]]; in [[Philadelphia]], [[Pennsylvania]]; in [[Bryn Mawr, Pennsylvania]], at [[Bryn Mawr College]]; and in [[Collegeville, Pennsylvania]], at [[Ursinus College]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.ursinus.edu/2014/headlines/abc-films-new-pilot-on-ursinus-campus/ |title=ABC Films New Pilot on Ursinus Campus |work=Ursinus College |date=March 14, 2014 |accessdate=March 28, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140322214050/http://news.ursinus.edu/2014/headlines/abc-films-new-pilot-on-ursinus-campus/ |archive-date=March 22, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> It was directed by [[Michael Offer]].<ref name=\"Director\">{{cite web |url=https://www.deadline.com/2014/01/abc-drama-pilots-warriors-how-to-get-away-with-murder-find-directors/ |title=ABC Drama Pilots 'Warriors' & 'How To Get Away With Murder' Find Directors |work=Deadline Hollywood |last=Andreeva |first=Nellie |date=January 31, 2014 |accessdate=May 5, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504214347/http://www.deadline.com/2014/01/abc-drama-pilots-warriors-how-to-get-away-with-murder-find-directors/ |archive-date=May 4, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> Production began on May 21, 2015, with [[Shonda Rhimes]] announcing on [[Twitter]] that [[Peter Nowalk]] and his writers were in full swing mapping the second season.<ref name=\"Rhimes\"/> The table read for the premiere occurred on July 14, 2015,<ref name=\"Davis\"/> with the title of the episode being revealed at the same time.<ref name=\"premiere title\"/>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"  style=\"text-align:center; float:right;\"\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" | Season\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" colspan=\"2\" | Critical response\n|-\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" | [[Rotten Tomatoes]]\n! style=\"padding:0 8px;\" | [[Metacritic]]\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#A91919;\"|\n| [[How to Get Away with Murder (season 1)#Reception|1]]\n| 85% (56 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s01|title=How to Get Away with Murder: Season 1 (2014\u20132015)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023200111/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s01/ |archive-date=October 23, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| 68 (30 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/season-1 |title=How to Get Away with Murder \u2013 Season 1 Reviews |website=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140927063322/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder |archive-date=September 27, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#353839;\"|\n| [[How to Get Away with Murder (season 2)#Reception|2]]\n| 93% (87 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s02|title=How to Get Away with Murder: Season 2 (2015\u20132016)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830163646/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s02/ |archive-date=August 30, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#64564A;\"|\n| [[How to Get Away with Murder (season 3)#Reception|3]]\n| 90% (30 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s03|title=How to Get Away with Murder: Season 3 (2016\u20132017)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304114721/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s03/ |archive-date=March 4, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#020202;\"|\n| [[How to Get Away with Murder (season 4)#Reception|4]]\n| 100% (8 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s04|title=How to Get Away with Murder: Season 4 (2017\u20132018)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171127193131/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s04/ |archive-date=November 27, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"width:12px; background:#860C16;\"|\n| [[How to Get Away with Murder (season 5)#Reception|5]]\n| 83% (6 reviews)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s05|title=How to Get Away with Murder: Season 5 (2018\u20132019)|website=[[Rotten Tomatoes]]|accessdate=April 3, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181102005417/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s05 |archive-date=November 2, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| {{n/a}}\n|}\n\nThe first season of ''How to Get Away with Murder'' received positive reviews, with most praising Viola Davis' performance. On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], it has an approval rating of 85% based on 56 reviews, with an average rating of 7.11/10. The site's critical consensus reads, \"''How to Get Away with Murder'' isn't conceptually original, but it delivers thrills with melodramatic twists and a captivating lead\".<ref name=\"S1RT\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s01/ |title=How to Get Away With Murder : Season 1 |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=September 1, 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161023200111/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder/s01/ |archive-date=October 23, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Metacritic]] gave the first season a score of 68 out of 100, based on 30 critics, indicating \"generally favorable reviews\".<ref name=\"S1MC\">{{cite web |url=https://www.metacritic.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder |title=How to Get Away With Murder : Season 1 |work=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=October 2, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140927063322/http://www.metacritic.com/tv/how-to-get-away-with-murder |archive-date=September 27, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nMary McNamara from ''[[Los Angeles Times]]'' wrote about Viola Davis' performance: \"...all eyes are on Davis, Tony winner and Oscar nominee. Magnetic and intimidating, Davis creates an implacable surface beneath which shimmers all manner of fleet and startled emotions. Desire and fear, certainty, self-doubt and resolve are conjured in an instant with the angle of a glance, the lowering of an eyelid and then released as if they were never there\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-how-to-get-away-with-murder-review-20140925-column.html |title='How to Get Away With Murder' keeps spotlight on Viola Davis |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |accessdate=March 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171214025435/http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-how-to-get-away-with-murder-review-20140925-column.html |archive-date=December 14, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''{{'}}s Melissa Maerz described Davis' performance as \"powerfully layered\".<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2014/10/15/how-get-away-murder |title=How to Get Away With Murder |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate=March 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161219202422/http://www.ew.com/article/2014/10/15/how-get-away-murder |archive-date=December 19, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> David Hinckle, from ''[[New York Daily News]]'', said that the series does not serve up enough fun unlike Rhimes' other series, ''[[Grey's Anatomy]]'' and ''[[Scandal (TV series)|Scandal]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/murder-tv-review-article-1.1951180 |title=How to Get Away With Murder |work=[[New York Daily News]] |accessdate=March 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305202616/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/tv/murder-tv-review-article-1.1951180 |archive-date=March 5, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> Frazier Moore, ''Associated Press'', wrote that the series \"promises to be twisty, wicked, dark and fun. And it stars Viola Davis, who brings life to a character of endless calculations and mystery\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kansascity.com/entertainment/tv/article1308483.html |title=These 10 new fall TV shows are worthy of a first-night look |publisher=[[Associated Press]] |accessdate=March 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180305142710/http://www.kansascity.com/entertainment/tv/article1308483.html |archive-date=March 5, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe second season also received positive reviews. On Rotten Tomatoes, it has an approval rating of 93% based on 87 reviews, with an average rating of 8.19/10. The site's critical consensus reads: \"Developing a stronger narrative this season, ''How to Get Away with Murder'' throws more improbable shocks and higher stakes into the mix, adding preposterous fuel to an addictive fire\".<ref name=\"S2RT\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s02/ |title=How to Get Away with Murder : Season 2 |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=April 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830163646/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s02/ |archive-date=August 30, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> Lesley Brock, ''Paste Magazine'', praised the second season writing: \"I would not put it past ''How to Get Away with Murder'', which has turned all other ABC show plot lines upside down on their heads and shown that nothing is impossible, to throw incest into an already haphazard mix\". Brock gave the season a score of 9 out of 10.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2015/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-review-its-called-the.html |title=How to Get Away with Murder Review: \"It's Called the Octopus\" |work=Paste Magazine |accessdate=March 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171130165729/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2015/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-review-its-called-the.html |archive-date=November 30, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref> Kyle Anderson, ''[[Entertainment weekly]]'', wrote that with Davis at the front the series can get away with anything.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/24/how-get-away-murder-season-2-premiere-ew-review |title=How to Get Away With Murder season 2 premiere: EW review |work=[[Entertainment weekly]] |accessdate=March 4, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171203075814/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/09/24/how-get-away-murder-season-2-premiere-ew-review/ |archive-date=December 3, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nThe third season, once again, also received positive reviews. On Rotten Tomatoes, it has a rating of 90% based on 30 reviews, with an average rating of 7.52/10. The site's critical consensus reads: \"Tense and taught, ''How to Get Away with Murder'' continues to step-up its game.\"<ref name=\"S3RT\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s03/ |title=How to Get Away with Murder : Season 3 |work=[[Rotten Tomatoes]] |accessdate=April 16, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304114721/https://www.rottentomatoes.com/tv/how_to_get_away_with_murder/s03/ |archive-date=March 4, 2017 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n====Critics' top ten lists====\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n{| class=\"collapsible collapsed\"\n! style=\"width:14em; background:#C4C3D0; text-align:left\"| 2014<ref>{{cite web |title=Best of 2014: Television Critic Top Ten Lists |work=Metacritic |url=https://www.metacritic.com/feature/tv-critics-pick-10-best-tv-shows-of-2014 |date=December 9, 2014 |access-date=December 30, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151106015332/http://www.metacritic.com/feature/tv-critics-pick-10-best-tv-shows-of-2014 |archive-date=November 6, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2|\n* No.&nbsp;9 ''[[The Salt Lake Tribune]]''\n* No.&nbsp;1 ''[[People Magazine]]''\n* No.&nbsp;9 ''[[Us Weekly]]''\n* No.&nbsp;10 ''[[Pittsburgh Post-Gazette ]]''\n* &nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Globe and Mail]]''\n* &nbsp;\u2013 ''[[American Film Institute]]''\n|}\n{{Col-end}}\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n{| class=\"collapsible collapsed\"\n! style=\"width:14em; background:#C4C3D0; text-align:left\"| 2015<ref>{{cite web |title=Best of 2015: Television Critic Top Ten Lists |work=Metacritic |url=https://www.metacritic.com/feature/critics-pick-the-top-10-best-tv-shows-of-2015 |date=December 8, 2015 |access-date=December 16, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706184930/http://www.metacritic.com/feature/critics-pick-the-top-10-best-tv-shows-of-2015 |archive-date=July 6, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=2|\n* No.&nbsp;10 ''[[TV Line]]''\n|}\n{{Col-end}}\n\n===Ratings===\n{{See also|List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes#Ratings}}\n\nThe series pilot on September 25 set a record for DVR playback viewers with 6 million, surpassing the January 27, 2014, record of 5.6 million set by the pilot of ''[[The Blacklist (TV series)|The Blacklist]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2014/tv/ratings/abcs-how-to-get-away-with-murder-premiere-sets-DVR-playback-record-1201317320/ |title=ABC's 'How to Get Away With Murder' Premiere Sets DVR Playback Record |work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |last=Kissell |first=Rick |accessdate=October 7, 2014 |date=September 30, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141007031350/http://variety.com/2014/tv/ratings/abcs-how-to-get-away-with-murder-premiere-sets-dvr-playback-record-1201317320/ |archive-date=October 7, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref> The series premiere had more than 14 million viewers on live broadcast, and over 20 million with DVR.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-breaks-736778 |title='How to Get Away With Murder' Breaks DVR Records |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=September 30, 2014 |accessdate=October 1, 2014 |first=Michael |last=O'Connell |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141003012904/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/how-get-away-murder-breaks-736778 |archive-date=October 3, 2014 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Season\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:12%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Timeslot ([[Eastern Time Zone#United States|ET]])\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Number of Episodes\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=2| Premiere\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=2| Finale\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\" rowspan=\"2\"| TV Season\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%; background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Overall rank\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%; background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| 18\u201349 rank\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9%; background:#ffdead;\" rowspan=\"2\"| Overall viewership\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\" span style=\"width:10%; font-size:smaller; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />(millions)\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:8%;\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\" span style=\"width:10%; font-size:smaller; line-height:100%;\"| Viewers<br />(millions)\n|-\n! style=\"background:#F9F9F9;text-align:center\"|[[How to Get Away with Murder (season 1)|1]]\n| rowspan=\"6\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | Thursdays<br />10:00 pm\n! 15\n| style=\"font-size:small; text-align: center;\"| {{Start date|2014|9|25}}\n! 14.12<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/10/12/gotham-has-biggest-adults-18-49-ratings-increase-gotham-red-band-society-top-percentage-gains-in-live-7-ratings-for-week-ending-september-28/313337/ |title='Gotham' Has Biggest Adults 18-49 Ratings Increase; 'Gotham' & 'Red Band Society' Top Percentage Gains & 'How To Get Away With Murder' Tops Viewer Gains in Live +7 Ratings for Week Ending September 28 |work=[[TV by the Numbers]] |last=Kondolojy |first=Amanda |accessdate=October 12, 2014 |date=October 12, 2014 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6TMI50T4Q?url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2014/10/12/gotham-ha