0|4|30}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = C5BAB4\n}}\n{{^|Episode list/sublist|How to Get Away with Murder (season 6)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 89\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 14\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      =\n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|7}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = C5BAB4\n}}\n{{^|Episode list/sublist|How to Get Away with Murder (season 6)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 90\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 15\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      =\n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|5|14}}\n |Viewers         = \n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = C5BAB4\n}}\n}}</onlyinclude>\n\n==Production==\n===Development===\nABC renewed ''How to Get Away with Murder'' for a sixth season on May 10, 2019.<ref name=\"Season 6 renewal\" /> After initial rumoring, it was announced on July 11, 2019, that the series would end with the upcoming season.<ref name=\"S6FinalSeason\" />\n\n=== Writing ===\nBesides the plans of following up with the previous season's [[cliffhanger]] on the whereabouts of Laurel Castillo and her son, other storylines are intended to be depicted in the sixth season, including Tegan Price's past, Michaela's father and his relationship to Annalise, and Vivian Maddox's life and background.<ref name=\"instagram S6 answers\">{{cite web |last1=Nowalk |first1=Pete |title=Week 2 in writers room and we have answers. #htgawm #season6 #buckleup (@peternowalk) |url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BxxPQh-J3i0/ |website=Instagram |accessdate=August 28, 2019}}</ref> According to series creator [[Peter Nowalk]], \"Every crime [that's been committed] will come up for grabs, be answered for, and will have to be paid for,\" he previews. \"Each character will have to decide what they're willing to do and to see if they're willing to sell other people out.\"<ref name=\"blake-announcement\">{{web cite|last1=Maloney|first1=Michael|title='How To Get Away With Murder' Casts 'When They See Us' Marsha Stephanie Blake for Season 6|url=https://www.tvinsider.com/809213/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-6-cast-marsha-stephanie-blake/|website=TV Insider|accessdate=August 30, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830070637/https://www.tvinsider.com/809213/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-6-cast-marsha-stephanie-blake/|archive-date=August 30, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to ''[[TVLine]]'', a different mystery will be introduced by the end of the [[season premiere]]. \"There will still be a [[flash forward]] in the first episode,\" Nowalk shares. \"It's a mystery that's really big, the biggest one we've done. It makes us get on a high-speed train [headed] toward the end of the show.\" In the meantime, Annalise is \"in bad shape\" following Laurel's disappearance, and Nowalk says \"we're going to see what Annalise's version of falling apart is.\" Plus, the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]]'s ongoing investigation into Annalise and company \"is front and center\". Nowalk teases, \"They know a lot, clearly. The question is, do they have the evidence to finally charge them? And who are they going to charge?\" Additionally, one of Michaela's birth parents will come into the picture in a storyline that Nowalk describes as \"very twisty, but also very emotional and surprising. I don't think the parent is going to be anyone you would expect.\"<ref name=\"TV Line Interview\">{{cite web |last1=Webb Mitovitch |first1=Matt |title=Fall TV Preview 2019: Spoilers on 37 Returning Favorites |url=https://tvline.com/gallery/fall-tv-2019-season-premiere-spoilers/htgawm-fall-tv-preview-2019/ |website=TV Line |accessdate=September 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923233135/https://tvline.com/gallery/fall-tv-2019-season-premiere-spoilers/htgawm-fall-tv-preview-2019/ |archive-date=September 23, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Casting===\nFor the sixth season, [[Timothy Hutton]] left the starring cast after his character's death.<ref>{{Cite press release|title=ABC\u2019s \u2018How to Get Away with Murder\u2019 Concludes With a Killer Sixth Season|date=July 11, 2019|location=United States|url=https://www.wdtvpress.com/abc/pressrelease/abcs-how-to-get-away-with-murder-concludes-with-a-killer-sixth-season/|access-date=April 10, 2020|publisher=[[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]}}</ref> [[Karla Souza]], who had portrayed Laurel Castillo since the series' inception, also exited the main cast, coinciding with Laurel and her son's disappearances in the previous season's finale.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tvline.com/2019/09/27/karla-souza-leaving-how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-6-laurel/ |title=''How to Get Away With Murder'' Final Season Twist: Original Cast Member Quietly Exits as Series Regular |date=September 27, 2019 |access-date=October 20, 2019 |work=TVLine |first=Michael |last=Ausiello |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002043522/https://tvline.com/2019/09/27/karla-souza-leaving-how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-6-laurel/ |archive-date=October 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with ''[[TV Insider]]'', Nowalk revealed that [[Marsha Stephanie Blake]] would guest star in the season in a \"great mystery role\",<ref name=\"blake-announcement\" /> later revealed to be that of Sam's ex-lover and Gabriel's mother, Vivian Maddox.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/10/03/how-to-get-away-with-murder-recap-season-6-episode-2/|title=HTGAWM Recap: Dirty Little Secret|last=Iannucci|first=Rebeca|date=October 3, 2019|website=TVLine|access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref> In October 2019, [[Cas Anvar]] joined the supporting cast as Robert Hsieh, \"an in-house lawyer of a popular dating app\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-casts-cas-anvar-raymond-lee-prodigal-son-1202757367/|title=\u2018How To Get Away With Murder\u2019 Casts Cas Anvar; Raymond Lee Joins \u2018Prodigal Son\u2019|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=October 11, 2019|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref> In January 2020, it was announced that [[Lauren Bowles]] had been cast as [[Assistant United States Attorney|Assistant U.S. Attorney]] Montes.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Iannucci |first1=Rebecca |title=HTGAWM Season 6 Adds True Blood's Lauren Bowles for Final Episodes |url=https://tvline.com/2020/01/24/how-to-get-away-with-murder-lauren-bowles-season-6-cast/ |website=[[TVLine]] |accessdate=March 29, 2020 |language=en |date=January 24, 2020}}</ref> In March 2020, [[Anne-Marie Johnson]] was cast as Kenda Strauss, a \"chic, high-powered defense attorney\", and [[Cicely Tyson]]'s return was announced.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2020/03/how-to-get-away-with-murder-anne-marie-johnson-cicely-tyson-season-six-1202893272/|title=\u2018How To Get Away With Murder\u2019: Anne-Marie Johnson To Recur, Cicely Tyson Returning For Final Season|last=N'Duka|first=Amanda|date=March 26, 2020|website=Deadline Hollywood|access-date=April 10, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===\nReviewing the first episode, Maureen Lee Lenker of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' complimented [[Viola Davis]]'s performance, writing, \"We will never get tired of watching her deliver week after week. To be honest, it\u2019s probably what we\u2019ll miss most about the show.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Lenker |first1=Maureen Lee |title='How to Get Away with Murder' premiere recap: Let the past die. Kill it if you have to. |url=https://ew.com/recap/how-to-get-away-with-murder-season-6-premiere/ |website=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |accessdate=March 29, 2020 |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref> ''[[The A.V. Club]]''{{'s}} Kayla Kumari Upadhyaya gave the first episode a \"B+\" rating, stating \"It would make sense for [the series] to go fully off the rails one last time in its final season, especially as it attempts to weave together every story that\u2019s still open. But maybe this will finally be the season that the show doesn\u2019t lose itself in its own madness.\"<ref>{{cite web |last1=Upadhyaya |first1=Kayla Kumari |title=At the beginning of the end, How To Get Away With Murder plays to its strengths |url=https://tv.avclub.com/at-the-beginning-of-the-end-how-to-get-away-with-murde-1838508213 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |accessdate=April 10, 2020 |language=en-us |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Ratings===\n{{Television episode ratings\n| width    = 99\n\n| title1    = [[#ep76|Say Goodbye]]\n| date1     = September 26, 2019\n| rs1       = 0.6/3\n| viewers1  = 2.43<ref name=\"6.01\"/>\n| dvr1      = 0.6\n| dvrv1     = 1.98\n| total1    = 1.2\n| totalv1   = 4.41<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-stumptown-tops-freshman-series-premieres-in-overall-raw-gains/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: 'Stumptown' Tops Freshman Series Premieres in Overall Raw Gains|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=October 8, 2019|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=October 8, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011040227/https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-stumptown-tops-freshman-series-premieres-in-overall-raw-gains/|archive-date=October 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n| title2    = [[#ep77|Vivian's Here]]\n| date2     = October 3, 2019\n| rs2       = 0.5/3\n| viewers2  = 2.56<ref name=\"6.02\"/>\n| dvr2      = 0.6\n| dvrv2     = 1.85\n| total2    = 1.1\n| totalv2   = 4.41<ref>{{cite web|url=https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-emergence-leads-broadcast-network-telecasts-in-viewer-percentage-gains/|title=Live+7 Weekly Ratings: 'Emergence' Leads Broadcast Network Telecasts in Viewer Percentage Gains|last=Pucci|first=Douglas|date=October 15, 2019|work=Programming Insider|accessdate=October 15, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101170433/https://programminginsider.com/live7-weekly-ratings-emergence-leads-broadcast-network-telecasts-in-viewer-percentage-gains/|archive-date=January 1, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>