}\n\n{{How to Get Away with Murder}}\n\n[[Category:2019 American television seasons]]\n[[Category:How to Get Away with Murder]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox television season\n| season_number        = 6\n| bgcolour             = #C5BAB4\n| image                = How to Get Away with Murder season 6 poster.jpg\n| image_upright        = \n| image_size           = \n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = Promotional poster\n| starring             = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Viola Davis]]\n* [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]]\n* [[Jack Falahee]]\n* [[Rome Flynn]]\n* [[Aja Naomi King]]\n* [[Matt McGorry]]\n* [[Conrad Ricamora]]\n* [[Amirah Vann]]\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]]\n* [[Liza Weil]]\n}}\n| country              = United States\n| num_episodes         = 11<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| network              = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]\n| first_aired          = {{Start date|2019|9|26}}\n| last_aired           = {{End date|present}}\n| episode_list         = List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes\n}}\nThe sixth and final season of the American television series ''[[How to Get Away with Murder]]'' premiered on September 26, 2019, and will conclude on May 14, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/how-to-get-away-with-murder/listings/|title=How to Get Away with Murder (abc) listings|website=The Futon Critic|accessdate=9 January 2020}}</ref> Ordered in May 2019 by [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]],<ref name=\"Season 6 renewal\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-6-abc-1202607397/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' Renewed For Season 6 By ABC|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=May 10, 2019|work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=May 10, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510165732/https://deadline.com/2019/05/how-to-get-away-with-murder-renewed-season-6-abc-1202607397/|archive-date=May 10, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\"S6FinalSeason\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/video/how-to-get-away-with-murder-end-season-6-abc/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' To End With Season 6 On ABC|website=Deadline Hollywood|first1=Denise|last1=Petski|first2=Nellie|last2=Andreeva|date=July 11, 2019|accessdate=July 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190711152428/https://deadline.com/video/how-to-get-away-with-murder-end-season-6-abc/|archive-date=July 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> the season will consist of fifteen episodes, like its predecessors, due to a deal made with [[Viola Davis]] that the series would be limited to only 15 or 16 episodes per season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://deadline.com/2014/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-blackish-full-season-1-orders-abc-848758/|title='How To Get Away With Murder' & 'Black-Ish': Full-Season Orders At ABC - Deadline|date=October 9, 2014|work=Deadline Hollywood|accessdate=November 1, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141024064124/http://deadline.com/2014/10/how-to-get-away-with-murder-blackish-full-season-1-orders-abc-848758/|archive-date=October 24, 2014|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Cast and characters==\n{{main|List of How to Get Away with Murder characters}}\n{{col-float}}\n===Main===\n* [[Viola Davis]] as [[Annalise Keating]]\n* [[Billy Brown (actor)|Billy Brown]] as Nate Lahey\n* [[Jack Falahee]] as [[Connor Walsh (character)|Connor Walsh]]\n* [[Rome Flynn]] as Gabriel Maddox\n* [[Aja Naomi King]] as Michaela Pratt\n* [[Matt McGorry]] as Asher Millstone\n* [[Conrad Ricamora]] as Oliver Hampton\n* [[Amirah Vann]] as Tegan Price\n* [[Charlie Weber (actor)|Charlie Weber]] as Frank Delfino\n* [[Liza Weil]] as [[Bonnie Winterbottom]]\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Marsha Stephanie Blake]] as Vivian Maddox <!-- 3 episodes -->\n* [[William R. Moses]] as Special Agent Lanford <!-- 7 episodes -->\n* Jennifer Jalene as Agent Avery Norris <!-- 5 episodes -->\n* [[Tom Verica]] as Sam Keating <!-- 3 episodes -->\n* Ray Campbell as Solomon Vick <!-- 4 episodes -->\n* [[Kelen Coleman]] as Chloe Millstone <!-- 6 episodes -->\n* [[Gerardo Celasco]] as Xavier Castillo <!-- 3 episodes -->\n* [[Mercedes Mason]] as Cora Duncan <!-- 3 episodes -->\n* [[Cas Anvar]] as Robert Hsieh <!-- 3 episodes -->\n* Quei Tann as Peyton Osborn <!-- 4 episodes -->\n* Jennifer Parsons as Lydia Millstone <!-- 4 episodes -->\n* Deborah Levin as Sara Gordon / Special Agent Pullock <!-- 3 episodes -->\n{{col-float-break}}\n===Guest===\n* [[Emily Bergl]] as Sally <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Kathleen Quinlan]] as Britt <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Esai Morales]] as Jorge Castillo <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Beverly Todd]] as Donna Fitzgerald <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Sam Anderson]] as Thomas Fitzgerald <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Jessica Marie Garcia]] as Rhonda Navarro <!-- 1 episode -->\n* Natalia del Riego as Marisol Diaz \n* Oscar Daniel Reyez as Hector Diaz \n* Dijon Talton as Ravi <!-- 2 episodes -->\n* [[Laura Innes]] as Governor Lynne Birkhead <!-- 2 episodes -->\n* [[Tess Harper]] as Sheila Miller <!-- 1 episodes -->\n* Teya Patt as Paula Gladden <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Cicely Tyson]] as Ophelia Harkness <!-- 2 episode -->\n* [[Karla Souza]] as Laurel Castillo <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Alfred Enoch]] as Wes Gibbins <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Cynthia Stevenson]] as Pam Walsh <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[D.W. Moffett]] as Jeff Walsh <!-- 1 episode -->\n* [[Lauren Bowles]] as Assistant U.S. Attorney Montes <!-- 2 episode -->\n* [[Kathleen York]] as Judge Martha Vitkay <!-- 2 episode -->\n* [[Anne-Marie Johnson]] as Kendra Strauss <!-- 2 episode -->\n{{col-float-end}}\n\n== Episodes ==\n{{See also|List of How to Get Away with Murder episodes}}\n<onlyinclude>{{Episode table |background=#C5BAB4 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=24 |director=14 |writer=25 |airdate=13 |viewers=9 |airdateR=<ref name=\"S6 airdates\">{{cite web |title=How to Get Away with Murder (ABC) Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/how-to-get-away-with-murder/listings/ |work=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=October 31, 2019}}</ref> |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list/sublist|How to Get Away with Murder (season 6)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 76\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n |Title           = Say Goodbye\n |DirectedBy      = [[Stephen Cragg]]\n |WrittenBy       = Sarah L. Thompson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|9|26}}\n |Viewers         = 2.43<ref name=\"6.01\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-september-26-2019/|title='Young Sheldon' adjusts up, 'A Million Little Things' and 'Evil' adjust down: Thursday final ratings|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|work=TV by the Numbers|date=September 27, 2019|accessdate=September 27, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190928220146/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-september-26-2019/|archive-date=September 28, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Following Laurel's disappearance and Emmett's death, a depressed Annalise gets high on cocaine. She voluntarily goes to rehabilitation under the fake name of Karen, befriends a woman named Sally and confesses she helped cover up Sam's murder. Encouraged by Sally's acceptance, she lets go of all her guilt by doing an exercise of self-forgiveness. Meanwhile, the Keating 3 are still dealing with Laurel's disappearance. Connor, Oliver, and Asher find evidence that Annalise knew Michaela's birth father, Dwight. Michaela gets closer to Gabriel and they have sex. Tegan takes Emmett's place as managing partner at Caplan & Gold, and Nate starts investigating her. Bonnie and Frank report Laurel's disappearance and Frank finds a key behind a framed photo of Laurel and Christopher. Annalise returns to Philadelphia and successfully recreates the self-forgiveness exercise with Connor, Michaela, Asher, and Oliver, but she is confronted about her connection with Michaela's dad. In an unknown period of time later, a flashforward shows Annalise's funeral being held. \n |LineColor       = C5BAB4\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|How to Get Away with Murder (season 6)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 77\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n |Title           = Vivian's Here\n |DirectedBy      = [[Michael Smith (director)|Mike Smith]]\n |WrittenBy       = Michael Russo\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|3}}\n |Viewers         = 2.56<ref name=\"6.02\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-october-3-2019/|title=Thursday Night Football adjusts up, 'A Million Little Things' adjusts down: Thursday final ratings|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 4, 2019|accessdate=October 4, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191005085704/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-october-3-2019/|archive-date=October 5, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Gabriel's mother, Vivian, confronts Annalise about her involvement in Sam's murder. Connor and Asher lead C&G's new case, which involves an 8-year-old, Hector, who\u2019s been separated from his immigrant mother and been traumatized by experiences with [[U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement|ICE]]. Helped by Tegan, they are able to put him on foster care. Frank asks Jorge Castillo in jail about Laurel's whereabouts, but he claims he knows nothing. Annalise reveals to Frank that the key he found belongs to a safe deposit box owned by Wes, and it contains information about their misdeeds. Frank, pretending to be Wes, gets access to an empty box. The clerk reveals that Laurel was the last person to access the box, three days prior. Annalise starts suspecting Tegan after Nate sees her talking to Vivian. Bonnie is fired from the DA's office after obtaining Vivian's sealed file illegally. Annalise visits Vivian and tells her Gabriel killed her boyfriend. Michaela locates her father with Oliver's help, but finds out he died on prison a year before. In a flashforward, a distraught Michaela sits in an interrogation room while two FBI agents walk in and inform her that her fingerprints were found on a murder weapon, a fire poker.\n |LineColor       = C5BAB4\n}}\n{{Episode list/sublist|How to Get Away with Murder (season 6)\n |EpisodeNumber   = 78\n |EpisodeNumber2  = 3\n |Title           = Do You Think I'm a Bad Man?\n |DirectedBy      = Catriona McKenzie\n |WrittenBy       = Daniel Robinson\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|10|10}} \n |Viewers         = 2.23<ref name=\"6.03\">{{cite web|url=https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-october-10-2019/|title='Grey's Anatomy' and 'Evil' adjust up: Thursday final ratings|last=Rejent|first=Joseph|work=TV by the Numbers|date=October 11, 2019|accessdate=October 11, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011205641/https://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/daily-ratings/thursday-final-ratings-october-10-2019/|archive-date=October 11, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n |ShortSummary    = Michaela heads the case of a woman who has been accused of helping her now dead husband rob money. After unsuccessful attempts, Michaela gets the client on probation with Annalise's help. Bonnie asks Tegan to hire her, who accepts, although initially reluctant. Through a cab driver, Frank finds an address Laurel was last seen and, there, is received by Xavier Castillo. After Bonnie and Tegan's intervention, Hector and his mother are allowed to stay together after being detained by ICE because of Connor. It is revealed that Tegan is married. Gabriel confesses to his mother that he killed her boyfriend, Paul, years ago. It is revealed that Vivian is actually spying for FBI. She gives Gabriel a set of recordings of Annalise's therapy sessions with Sam. Gabriel shows a particular tape to Michaela which he thinks is about her father, who is actually a lawyer. Nate is offered a deal to close his father's case in exchange of spying on Annalise. In a f