st Albums of 2019|date=2019-12-16|website=NME.com|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-01-02}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]''\n| The 34 Best Albums of 2019\n| {{center|9}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2019/12/best-albums-of-2019.html|title=The 50 Best Albums of 2019|last=Staff|first=Paste|date=2019-12-10|website=pastemagazine.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-02}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|''[[Townsquare Media|PopCrush]]''\n| 25 Best Pop Albums of 2019\n| {{N/A}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://popcrush.com/best-albums-2019/|title=The 25 Best Albums of 2019|last=Staff|first=PopCrush|website=PopCrush|language=en|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| The 50 Best Albums of 2019\n| {{center|6}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-albums-2019-914750/|title=The 50 Best Albums of 2019|last=Vozick-Levinson|first=Jonathan Bernstein,Jon Blistein,Jon Dolan,Patrick Doyle,Brenna Ehrlich,Suzy Exposito,Jon Freeman,David Fricke,Kory Grow,Will Hermes,Christian Hoard,Charles Holmes,Joseph Hudak,Brendan Klinkenberg,Elias Leight,Angie Martoccio,Claire Shaffer,Rob Sheffield,Hank Shteamer,Brittany Spanos,Simon|last2=Shteamer|first2=Hank|date=2019-12-05|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| The 200 Best Albums of the 2010s\n| {{center|69}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-lists/best-albums-2010s-ranked-913997/|title=The 100 Best Albums of the 2010s|last=Grow|first=Jon Dolan,Brittany Spanos,Simon Vozick-Levinson,Rob Sheffield,Charles Holmes,Christian Hoard,Joseph Hudak,Elias Leight,Suzy Exposito,Will Hermes,Angie Martoccio,David Browne,Hank Shteamer,Jon Freeman,Claire Shaffer,Brenna Ehrlich,Jonathan Bernstein,Jon Blistein,Nick Catucci,Brendan Klinkenberg,Danny Schwartz,Kory|last2=Portwood|first2=Jerry|date=2019-12-03|website=Rolling Stone|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|''[[Uproxx]]''\n| The Best Albums of 2019\n| {{center|8}}\n| {{center|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uproxx.com/music/best-albums-2019-ranked/|title=The Best Albums Of 2019|date=2019-12-02|website=UPROXX|language=en-US|access-date=2019-12-10}}</ref>}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''Cuz I Love You'' debuted at number six on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] with 41,000 [[album-equivalent unit]]s, of which 24,000 were pure album sales. It is Lizzo's first album to chart on the ''Billboard'' 200.<ref name=\"BB200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8509026/billie-eilish-returns-no-1-album-billboard-200|title=Billie Eilish's 'When We All Fall Asleep, Where Do We Go?' Returns to No. 1 on Billboard 200 Albums Chart|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=April 28, 2019|accessdate=April 29, 2019}}</ref> It then repeaked at number six on the charting week ending on June 27, 2019. It has stayed in the top 10 for 15 weeks after its release. The album reached number 4 in its 19th week on the chart dated September 7, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8529232/lizzo-cuz-i-love-you-album-top-5-billboard-200-chart|title=Lizzo's 'Cuz I Love You' Album Hits Top 5 on Billboard 200 Chart|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-09-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8518137/the-raconteurs-first-no-1-album-billboard-200|title=The Raconteurs Land First No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Help Us Stranger'|work=Billboard|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=June 30, 2019|accessdate=July 3, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]] and [[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Try the TIDAL Web Player |url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/108639914/credits |website=listen.tidal.com |accessdate=24 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://repertoire.bmi.com/StartPage.aspx|title=BMI {{!}} Repertoire Search|publisher=[[Broadcast Music, Inc.|BMI]]|accessdate=December 24, 2019|at=Select \"TITLE\", type \"Song\" in the search engine, and click \"Search\".}}</ref>\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Cuz I Love You''\n| extra_column = Producer(s)\n| title1 = [[Cuz I Love You (song)|Cuz I Love You]]\n| writer1 = {{hlist|[[Lizzo|Melissa Jefferson]]|[[X Ambassadors|Sam Harris]]|[[X Ambassadors|Casey Harris]]|[[X Ambassadors|Adam Levin]]|Russ Flynn}}\n| extra1 = [[X Ambassadors]]\n| length1 = 3:00\n| title2 = Like a Girl\n| writer2 = {{hlist|Jefferson|[[Oak Felder|Warren \"Oak\" Felder]]|[[Sean Douglas (songwriter)|Sean Douglas]]}}\n| extra2 = [[Oak Felder|Oak]]\n| length2 = 3:05\n| title3 = [[Juice (Lizzo song)|Juice]]\n| writer3 = {{hlist|Jefferson|[[Ricky Reed|Eric Frederic]]|[[R. City|Theron Thomas]]|Sam Sumser|Sean Small}}\n| extra3 = {{hlist|[[Ricky Reed]]|Nate Mercureau{{ref|b|[b]}}}}\n| length3 = 3:15\n| title4 = Soulmate\n| writer4 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Felder|Douglas}}\n| extra4 = Oak\n| length4 = 2:55\n| title5 = Jerome\n| writer5 = {{hlist|Jefferson|S. Harris|C. Harris|Levin}}\n| extra5 = X Ambassadors\n| length5 = 3:52 \n| title6 = Crybaby\n| writer6 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Frederic|Thomas|Mercureau}}\n| extra6 = {{hlist|Reed|Mercureau}}\n| length6 = 2:56\n| title7 = [[Tempo (Lizzo song)|Tempo]]\n| note7 = featuring [[Missy Elliott]]\n| writer7 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Dan Farber|Frederic|Tobias Wincorn|Thomas|[[Raymond Scott]]|Antonio Cuna|[[Missy Elliott|Melissa Elliott]]}}\n| extra7 = {{hlist|Ricky Reed|Sweater Beats|Tobias Wincorn|Farber|Lizzo|Mercureau{{ref|a|[a]}}}}\n| length7 = 2:55\n| title8 = Exactly How I Feel\n| note8 = featuring [[Gucci Mane]]\n| writer8 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Thomas|Mike Sabath|[[Gucci Mane|Radric Davis]]}}\n| extra8 = {{hlist|X Ambassadors|Sabath}}\n| length8 = 2:23\n| title9 = Better in Color\n| writer9 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Felder|Michael Pollack|Trevor \"Downtown\" Brown|William Zaire|Simmons}}\n| extra9 = {{hlist|Oak|Downtown Trevor Brown{{ref|a|[a]}}|Zaire Koalo{{ref|a|[a]}}}}\n| length9 = 2:13\n| title10 = Heaven Help Me\n| writer10 = {{hlist|Jefferson|C. Harris|S. Harris|Levin}}\n| extra10 = X Ambassadors\n| length10 = 3:22\n| title11 = Lingerie\n| writer11 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Frederic|Mercereau|Thomas}}\n| extra11 = {{hlist|Ricky Reed|Mercureau}}\n| length11 = 3:22\n| total_length = 33:18\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Cuz I Love You''{{nobold|&nbsp;\u2013 Deluxe version}}\n| extra_column = Producer\n| title12 = [[Boys (Lizzo song)|Boys]]\n| length12 = 2:53\n| writer12 = {{hlist|Lil Aaron|Mercereau|Frederic|Jefferson}}\n| extra12 = {{hlist|Mercereau|Reed}}\n| title13 = [[Truth Hurts (song)|Truth Hurts]]\n| length13 = 2:53\n| writer13 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Frederic|Amina Patrice Bogle-Barriteau|[[Jesse Saint John]]|Steven Cheung}}\n| extra13 = {{hlist|Reed|Tele{{ref|a|[a]}}}}\n| title14 = [[Water Me (Lizzo song)|Water Me]]\n| length14 = 3:06\n| writer14 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Frederic|[[The Monsters and the Strangerz|Clarence Coffee Jr.]]|[[E. Kidd Bogart]]|Farhad Samadzada|Morris Wittenberg|[[Nneka (singer)|Nneka Lucia Egbuna]]|Wincorn}}\n| extra14 = {{hlist|Reed|Wincorn{{ref|b|[b]}}}}\n| total_length = 42:10\n}}\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Cuz I Love You''{{nobold|&nbsp;\u2013 Super deluxe}}\n| extra_column = Producer (s)\n| title15 = [[Good as Hell]]\n| length15 = 2:39\n| writer15 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Frederic}}\n| extra15 = {{hlist|Lizzo|Reed}}\n| title16 = [[Good as Hell]] (Remix)\n| note16 = featuring [[Ariana Grande]]\n| length16 = 2:39\n| writer16 = {{hlist|Jefferson|Frederic|[[Ariana Grande]]}}\n| extra16 = {{hlist|Lizzo|Reed}}\n| total_length = 47:18\n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n* <sup>{{note|a|[a]}}</sup> signifies a co-[[record producer|producer]].\n* <sup>{{note|b|[b]}}</sup> signifies an additional producer.\n* \"Water Me\" contains elements from \"I Am Free, No Dope For Me\" written by Morris Wittenberg and from \"My Home\" written by Nneka Lucia Egbuna and Farhad Samadzada.\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from album\u2019s liner notes.<ref>{{cite AV media notes|title= Cuz I Love You (Deluxe Edition) |year= 2019 |type= booklet |publisher= Nice Life, [[Atlantic Records|Atlantic]]}}</ref>\n\n{{div col}}\n* Downtown Trevor Brown \u2014 co-producer <small>(track 9)</small>\n* Harry Burr \u2014 mixing assistant <small>(track 5)</small>\n* [[The Monsters and the Strangerz|Clarence Coffee Jr.]] \u2014 additional vocals <small>(track 14)</small>\n* Michael Cordone \u2014 trumpet <small>(track 3)</small>\n* Scott Desmarais \u2014 mixing assistant <small>(tracks 1-4, 6-11, 13)</small>\n* [[Missy Elliott]] \u2014 rap and additional vocals <small>(track 7)</small>\n* Shaina Evoniuk \u2014 viola <small>(track 11)</small>\n* Dan Farber \u2014 co-producer <small>(track 7)</small>\n* [[Oak Felder]] \u2014 producer <small>(tracks 2, 4, 9)</small>\n* Robin Florent \u2014 mixing assistant <small>(tracks 1-4, 6-11, 13)</small>\n* Chris Galland \u2014 mix engineer <small>(track 13)</small>\n* [[Chris Gehringer]] \u2014 mastering <small>(tracks 1-4, 6-13)</small>\n* [[Gucci Mane]] \u2014 rap <small>(track 8)</small>\n* Lemar Guillary \u2014 trombone <small>(track 3)</small>\n* [[Victor Indrizzo]] \u2014 drums and percussion <small>(track 3)</small>\n* Rouble Kapoor \u2014 assistant engineer <small>(track 3)</small>\n* Zaire Koalo \u2014 co-producer <small>(track 9)</small>\n* [[Joe LaPorta]] \u2014 mastering <small>(track 5)</small>\n* Trevor Lawrence Jr. \u2014 drums <small>(track 11)</small>\n* [[Lizzo]] \u2014 vocals <small>(all tracks)</small>, producer <small>(7)</small>, synthesizer <small>(14)</small>, executive producer\n* Bill Malina \u2014 engineer <small>(tracks 3, 11)</small>\n* [[Manny Marroquin]] \u2014 mixing <small>(tracks 1-4, 6-11, 13)</small>\n* Asha Maura \u2014 backing vocals <small>(track 3)</small>\n* [[Andrew Maury]] \u2014\u00a0mixing <small>(track 5)</small>\n* Jesse McGinty \u2014 saxophone <small>(track 3)